# Magic `/ui` Skill

When the user asks for `/ui` or requests a new React UI component:

1. Use the MCP tool `21st_magic_component_builder`.
2. Build `standaloneRequestQuery` with explicit style guidance to match the existing page palette, typography, spacing, and radius.
3. Prefer component names and structure that fit the current codebase conventions.
4. After receiving generated code, integrate it into project files and wire imports/usages.
5. If generated code depends on missing `shadcn/ui` primitives, install only the needed primitives.

When the user asks to improve an existing UI block (not full-page redesign), use `21st_magic_component_refiner`.
